caption: The food is delicious and good price, and staff are so nice. My tip, the more topping you add, the more tasty it is ☺️ my favorite is shrimp, char siu pork, bacon, mushrooms, corn, and scallions
(Translated by Google) It’s delicious, but the portion of meat is a little bit less, so you must add meat  (Original) 好吃 就是肉的分量少了点 一定要加肉
This place has really good steam rolls for a very good price. They’re delicious! Note that they are Cash Only.
Love it! So so yum!! 😭It’s the flavor of my hometown

Steam rice roll is very delicious.  Reminds me of the vietnamese banh cuon my grandmother use to make with the bamboo steamer.  Very authentic flavor. Must go to. Be aware it is a long wait.  Expect 30 mins wait.

Love this place! The rice rolls are all delicious but my all time favorite rice rolls are the shrimp with salted egg and char siu rice rolls. The portions are big and you can’t beat the price. On average, I’ve visited once a week since they’ve opened and order at minimum 3 rice rolls! My only wish is that they closed later.

Just found out about this new gem in Bensonhurst and have gone twice already in the past week!! The steam rice rolls here are so good and great value as well. I’ve tried Hometown Rice Roll, Curry Fish Ball Rice Roll, Beef Rice Roll and Shrimp w/Salted Egg Yolk Steam rice Roll. Definitely a must try and I’d gladly get the steam rice rolls here over the Chinese bakery ones anyway.

Just found this hidden gem in bensonhurst yesterday while I was at work! I watched their YouTube video and it had me sold. The menu is small and inexpensive, and the amount of steam rolls you get for the price is perfect! (chefs kiss) I got the chicken steam rolls with the cilantro, scallions, and bean sprouts. Im coming back tomorrow and will most definitely try the whole menu!

One of the best Cantonese-style Steam rice rolls (Cheong Fun) in Brooklyn. The rice for the roll is ground daily using an electric power stone mill. Made fresh every day. Its priced very generous in time like this, for me with 1 order, it really fills me up at first I thought they made a mistake and putting 2 orders in one, I ask the boss, she said that is 1 order. The texture is smooth and thin. It's a simple 2 pages menu with 1 listing all the drinks and second, provide all the Rice rolls and you can customize, also the choice for Hong Kong-style curry fish balls. Only wish they have one in Staten Island, even after the next day, just microwave with a wet napkin and it's damn Good again. For me they might need to improve the meat one.
